<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3318] Split rollback leaves parent with writesEnabled=false</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3318</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I saw a split rollback today, and it left the region in a state where it was able to take writes, but wasn&apos;t able to flush or compact. It&apos;s printing this message every few milliseconds:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;NOT flushing memstore for region xxx., flushing=false, writesEnabled=false
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see why, writesEnabled is never set back in HRegion.initialize:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// See &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; region is meant to run read-only.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.regionInfo.getTableDesc().isReadOnly()) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.writestate.setReadOnly(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead it needs to pass isReadOnly into the setReadOnly method to work correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it should go in 0.90.0 if there&apos;s a new RC.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
